---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const lastUpdated = "June 11, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="The terms under which you can use the practicestartupservices.com website and the content it provides."
  noIndex={false}
>
  <section class="border-b border-ink/8 py-14 lg:py-20 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10 opacity-[0.04]" aria-hidden="true">
      <svg width="100%" height="100%" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <defs>
          <pattern id="bp-grid-terms" x="0" y="0" width="48" height="48" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
            <path d="M 48 0 L 0 0 0 48" fill="none" stroke="hsl(var(--ink-800))" stroke-width="1" />
          </pattern>
        </defs>
        <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#bp-grid-terms)" />
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="container-site relative">
      <div class="max-w-prose mx-auto">
        <div class="phase-label text-bronze-700 mb-5">Legal</div>
        <h1 class="font-display text-display-xl font-medium text-ink mb-3 text-balance">
          Terms of Use.
        </h1>
        <p class="font-mono text-label text-graphite-600 tracking-[0.18em] uppercase">
          Last updated: {lastUpdated}
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 lg:py-20">
    <div class="container-site">
      <div class="prose-editorial">
        <p class="text-lede text-graphite-800 leading-relaxed mb-8 text-pretty">
          These terms apply to your use of practicestartupservices.com and the content we publish.
          By using the site, you agree to these terms.
        </p>

        <h2>What this site is.</h2>
        <p>
          PracticeStartupServices.com is a content + services website for medical professionals
          planning or operating an independent practice. Content is published for general
          information; it is not legal, tax, medical, or financial advice for your specific
          situation. For advice you can rely on, talk to a qualified professional — including, if
          you'd like, our team via a consultation.
        </p>

        <h2>Not professional advice.</h2>
        <p>
          The content on this site — including all phase guides, state pages, specialty pages,
          checklists, cost guides, and AI-companion responses — is general information based on
          common practice scenarios. State laws vary, payer rules change, and every practice has
          its own specifics. Do not rely on this site alone for decisions that materially affect
          your business, your patients, or your legal exposure.
        </p>

        <h2>The Architect AI companion.</h2>
        <p>
          The Architect is an AI tool trained to surface relevant phase guidance and route you to
          appropriate resources. It is not a substitute for professional advice. It may produce
          incorrect or incomplete answers. Verify anything material before acting on it. If you
          want a real plan for your situation, schedule a consultation with our team.
        </p>

        <h2>Third-party links and tools.</h2>
        <p>
          We link to third-party sites including Metolius's Medicare lookup tools and external
          professional resources. We do not control these sites and are not responsible for their
          content, accuracy, or availability. Their privacy policies and terms apply to your use
          of them.
        </p>

        <h2>Your use of the site.</h2>
        <p>
          You agree not to use the site to harm others, attempt unauthorized access, scrape at
          rates that affect performance, or copy substantial portions of our content for
          republication without permission. Linking to our pages and quoting reasonable excerpts
          with attribution is welcome.
        </p>

        <h2>Intellectual property.</h2>
        <p>
          The content, design, brand marks, and original materials on this site are the property
          of Practice Startup Services unless otherwise noted. Specific medical terminology,
          regulatory references, and government tools (Medicare fee schedules, CMS forms, state
          program names) are referenced in their original context.
        </p>

        <h2>Disclaimers.</h2>
        <p>
          The site is provided "as is" and "as available." We make no warranties about
          uninterrupted operation, error-free content, or fitness for any particular purpose. We
          may update or remove content at any time without notice.
        </p>

        <h2>Limitation of liability.</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent allowed by law, Practice Startup Services is not liable for any
          indirect, incidental, consequential, or special damages arising from your use of the
          site or reliance on its content. If you have a claim, the maximum total liability is
          limited to fees you have paid us in the twelve months preceding the claim, or $100,
          whichever is greater.
        </p>

        <h2>Governing law.</h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the laws of the state where Practice Startup Services
          maintains its principal place of business, without regard to conflicts-of-law
          principles. Disputes will be resolved in the courts located in that jurisdiction.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to these terms.</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these terms as our practices evolve. The "Last updated" date at the top
          reflects the most recent version. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes
          acceptance of the updated terms.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact.</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these terms:
          <a href="mailto:hello@practicestartupservices.com" class="underline text-ink hover:text-bronze-700">hello@practicestartupservices.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
